We are deeply grateful to the park managers and other personnel,
including especially those who care for the diversity of the gardens and
the integrity of the woodlots in the various parts of Campinas. Marcio
Uehara-Prado, Francini Osses, Regina Alonso, Artur N. Furegatti, Gustavo
Accacio, Renato Fernandes, Rafael Andrade and Danilo Bandini assisted in
the censuses of butterflies in the city and the suburbs. Mario Belloni
Jr. kindly gave permission to use the base photo for Figure 1 (lower).
The Instituto Agronomico de Campinas authorized work in sites MJ and CS,
the Fundacao Mata da Santa Genebra encouraged our long-term studies in
SG, and the Condominio Colinas do Atibaia facilitated access to RC. For
general inspiration and guidance, we are indebted to Alexandre Ruszczyk,
Jacqueline J.S. Rodrigues, and Gustavo Accacio. Dionete Santin helped
greatly in the choice, historical aspects, and vegetation analyses
(1999) of the Campinas city parks and other reserves. Two anonymous
referees contributed many helpful suggestions to the final version of
this paper. The field work and publication of this paper were partially
funded by the BIOTA/FAPESP program (Grants 98/05101-8 and 00/01484-1).
